## When Making Changes
1. Always read the existing code first
2. Understand the context and dependencies
3. Make small, incremental changes
4. Test each change before moving to the next
5. Update documentation if needed
6. Follow the security best practices
7. Keep the code clean and maintainable

## Questions to Ask Before Coding
- Is this change necessary?
- Does it follow security best practices?
- Will it break existing functionality?
- Is it properly tested?
- Is it documented?
- Does it follow the project conventions?
